OL,3,CBy-election date proposed in Guernsey
OL,4,Cafter Le Tocq's resignation
OL,6,FA by-election could be held in
OL,7,FGuernsey this April to fill the
OL,8,FStates' empty seat left by Jonathan Le
OL,9,FTocq.
OL,11,FThe disgraced politician resigned last
OL,12,Fyear after pleading guilty to 15
OL,13,Fsexual offences, including creating
OL,14,Fmore than 2,400 indecent images - he
OL,15,Fwas jailed for nine years in January.
OL,17,FLe Tocq was replaced as External
OL,18,FRelations Lead by Deputy Steve Falla,
OL,19,Fbut his seat in the States of
OL,20,FDeliberation is still vacant.
