OL,3,CBy-election date proposed in Guernsey
OL,4,Cafter Le Tocq's resignation
OL,6,FIf proposals by the States' Assembly
OL,7,Fand Constitution Committee (SACC) are
OL,8,Fapproved by the Assembly later this
OL,9,Fmonth, then a by-election will be held
OL,10,Fon Wednesday 29 April.
OL,12,FIt is predicted to cost #75,000 and
OL,13,Fcomes less than a year since
OL,14,FGuernsey's last General Election.
OL,16,FUnder the plans, those already
OL,17,Fregistered on the Electoral Roll for
OL,18,Fthat poll would not need to sign up
OL,19,Fagain.
OL,21,FOther proposed details include:
